01:38:11,553 --> 01:38:13,138
When I came back
from the wars,

784
01:38:13,222 --> 01:38:15,182
I carried with me
the stench of death

785
01:38:15,349 --> 01:38:17,476
and the anger of the lost.

786
01:38:18,268 --> 01:38:22,398
I wasn't worth saving,
that's for sure.
But she did so anyway.

787
01:38:24,358 --> 01:38:26,443
And I loved her so much.

788
01:38:27,986 --> 01:38:29,780
I loved her more than
anyone or anything.

789
01:38:29,947 --> 01:38:33,826
And then I let her
out of my sight
and she was gone.

790
01:38:37,746 --> 01:38:40,290
And I became myself again.

791
01:38:40,457 --> 01:38:42,751
A self I never cared for.

792
01:38:47,756 --> 01:38:49,133
Until you.

793
01:38:52,886 --> 01:38:55,097
See, you remind me of her.

794
01:38:57,349 --> 01:38:59,935
Her heart. Her spirit.

795
01:39:03,647 --> 01:39:06,358
But now you, too,
have gone.

796
01:39:07,025 --> 01:39:10,571
You both deserved better,
and I'm so sorry I failed you.

797
01:39:11,405 --> 01:39:13,031
I'm so sorry.

798
01:39:21,039 --> 01:39:23,542
But you'll be a queen
in heaven now

799
01:39:24,418 --> 01:39:26,336
and sit among the angels.

800
01:40:14,551 --> 01:40:16,178
She died for us!

801
01:40:16,803 --> 01:40:18,388
For our cause!

802
01:40:18,555 --> 01:40:20,432
We cannot just hide
behind these walls

803
01:40:20,599 --> 01:40:22,476
and watch this land
die with her!

804
01:40:23,393 --> 01:40:25,646
Your grief clouds
your judgment, my son.

805
01:40:27,689 --> 01:40:30,734
My grief makes me
see clearer, Father.

806
01:40:33,570 --> 01:40:36,949
My duty is
to protect those people
who come to me for help.

807
01:40:37,991 --> 01:40:40,702
I will defend them
to the last drop of my blood,

808
01:40:41,787 --> 01:40:44,039
but I will not
abandon these walls.

809
01:41:05,185 --> 01:41:07,062
The spell is lifted.

810
01:41:38,468 --> 01:41:40,053
Death has favored you.

811
01:41:40,220 --> 01:41:41,930
Death favors no man.

812
01:41:42,931 --> 01:41:43,974
We must ride

813
01:41:44,141 --> 01:41:47,519
like thundering waves
under the tattered battle
flag of my father.

814
01:41:47,853 --> 01:41:49,104
You must rest.

815
01:41:50,522 --> 01:41:52,107
We have rested
long enough.

816
01:42:01,116 --> 01:42:03,702
Frost to fire
and fire to frost.

817
01:42:08,749 --> 01:42:10,709
Iron will melt.

818
01:42:14,254 --> 01:42:17,382
But it will writhe
inside of itself!

819
01:42:20,385 --> 01:42:21,470
All these years

820
01:42:22,804 --> 01:42:24,640
all I've known is darkness.

821
01:42:26,892 --> 01:42:30,562
But I have never seen
a brighter light than when
my eyes just opened.

822
01:42:32,439 --> 01:42:35,567
And I know that light
burns in all of you!

823
01:42:37,819 --> 01:42:38,904
Those embers

824
01:42:40,238 --> 01:42:41,907
must turn to flame.

825
01:42:43,992 --> 01:42:46,453
Iron into sword!

826
01:42:46,578 --> 01:42:48,580
I will become your weapon!

827
01:42:49,581 --> 01:42:50,999
Forged by the fierce fire

828
01:42:51,166 --> 01:42:53,293
that I know is
in your hearts!

829
01:42:55,420 --> 01:42:57,798
For I have seen
what she sees.

830
01:42:59,591 --> 01:43:01,635
I know what she knows.

831
01:43:04,012 --> 01:43:05,931
I can kill her.

832
01:43:09,935 --> 01:43:11,770
And I'd rather die today

833
01:43:13,021 --> 01:43:16,149
than live another day
of this death!

834
01:43:18,860 --> 01:43:20,946
And who will ride with me?

835
01:43:21,863 --> 01:43:23,031
Who will be my brother?

836
01:43:23,657 --> 01:43:25,117
Aye!

837
01:44:11,747 --> 01:44:13,498
Farewell, Princess.

838
01:44:37,689 --> 01:44:39,024
Where are they?

839
01:44:39,191 --> 01:44:40,901
Amassed on the cliffs.

840
01:44:41,067 --> 01:44:43,028
Their numbers
have swollen.

841
01:44:43,361 --> 01:44:46,114
They say the King's
standard flies again.

842
01:44:47,073 --> 01:44:48,617
Then let them come.

843
01:44:49,367 --> 01:44:53,580
And let them
break their skulls
on these stone walls

844
01:44:53,955 --> 01:44:56,208
and bring me my prize.

845
01:45:12,724 --> 01:45:13,767
My lord,

846
01:45:13,892 --> 01:45:16,061
we only have a few hours
before the tide comes in.

847
01:45:16,228 --> 01:45:18,396
Not long enough
to breach the castle walls.

848
01:45:18,563 --> 01:45:19,981
Is there no other way in?

849
01:45:20,148 --> 01:45:21,441
There is another way.

850
01:45:25,320 --> 01:45:27,489
Hi-ho, lads,
it's off to work.

851
01:45:27,656 --> 01:45:30,534
If he starts whistling,
I'll smash his face in.

852
01:45:35,580 --> 01:45:36,581
Yes.

853
01:45:36,832 --> 01:45:38,834
We're promised gold
and what do we get?

854
01:45:39,000 --> 01:45:40,085
Poo!

855
01:45:40,252 --> 01:45:42,045
How low has
the dwarf race sunk?

856
01:45:45,090 --> 01:45:46,633
That looks like one of mine.

857
01:45:46,967 --> 01:45:47,968
Hold this!

858
01:46:09,823 --> 01:46:11,241
All right.

859
01:46:11,324 --> 01:46:13,076
The gatehouse
is 50 yards to the right.

860
01:46:13,243 --> 01:46:14,953
And there's a whole
army out there.

861
01:46:15,287 --> 01:46:17,330
Six dwarves
against an army?

862
01:46:18,123 --> 01:46:20,000
I like them odds.

863
01:46:22,127 --> 01:46:24,588
We must ride now.
The portcullis will be open.

864
01:46:30,927 --> 01:46:33,930
So, you're back from the dead
and instigating the masses.

865
01:46:37,809 --> 01:46:40,020
You look very
fetching in mail.

866
01:46:44,524 --> 01:46:45,942
We ride!

867
01:46:50,155 --> 01:46:53,783
All right.
We move as one.

868
01:46:58,288 --> 01:46:59,497
After you.

869
01:47:14,638 --> 01:47:17,474
Hey, go, go, go.

870
01:48:35,552 --> 01:48:36,761
Sorry.

871
01:48:40,890 --> 01:48:41,891
What's happening, Coll?

872
01:48:42,142 --> 01:48:43,309
They're on the beach!

873
01:48:50,066 --> 01:48:51,276
Release!

874
01:49:32,150 --> 01:49:34,152
Ready! Release!

875
01:49:39,157 --> 01:49:40,325
Release!

876
01:49:54,839 --> 01:49:57,175
Go, go, go!

877
01:50:00,720 --> 01:50:02,597
The summit's breached!

878
01:50:09,687 --> 01:50:11,022
Back here, lads!
Come on!

879
01:50:11,189 --> 01:50:12,690
Get back to it!

880
01:50:25,703 --> 01:50:27,664
Pull!
Nion, get on that rope!

881
01:50:27,831 --> 01:50:29,582
Come on!
Go on!

882
01:50:30,708 --> 01:50:31,751
Quert!

883
01:50:34,254 --> 01:50:35,296
It's a massacre
down there!

884
01:50:35,380 --> 01:50:37,173
Gort, on that rope!

885
01:50:39,050 --> 01:50:40,385
We must turn back!

886
01:50:40,677 --> 01:50:43,179
No! I gave them my word!

887
01:50:43,346 --> 01:50:44,681
It's over!
Get on now!

888
01:50:49,894 --> 01:50:50,895
She's moving.

889
01:50:52,397 --> 01:50:53,606
You done it, lads!

890
01:50:59,028 --> 01:51:00,697
Charge!

891
01:51:01,322 --> 01:51:02,323
Ya!

892
01:51:12,208 --> 01:51:14,836
Form! Form!

893
01:53:01,276 --> 01:53:02,694
William!

894
01:55:27,213 --> 01:55:30,508
Come and avenge
your father

895
01:55:31,175 --> 01:55:34,595
who was too weak
to raise his sword.

896
01:55:39,600 --> 01:55:40,810
Ah.

897
01:55:53,865 --> 01:55:54,866
Go on.

898
01:55:56,200 --> 01:55:58,453
Watch them die.

899
01:56:14,552 --> 01:56:16,220
How does it feel,

900
01:56:16,387 --> 01:56:19,223
knowing you were
the one who led them
to their deaths?

901
01:56:19,640 --> 01:56:20,641
You see?

902
01:56:20,725 --> 01:56:23,436
We're not that different,
are we?

903
01:56:26,105 --> 01:56:27,732
I'm everything you're not.

904
01:56:50,922 --> 01:56:53,799
You cannot defeat me!

905
01:56:54,926 --> 01:56:58,054
I've lived too many lives.

906
01:56:58,471 --> 01:57:00,932
Ravaged entire kingdoms.

907
01:57:01,349 --> 01:57:05,478
I have been given powers
that you could
not even fathom!

908
01:57:08,272 --> 01:57:09,690
I will never stop.

909
01:57:11,108 --> 01:57:12,527
Never.

910
01:57:14,654 --> 01:57:17,281
I will give
this wretched world

911
01:57:17,448 --> 01:57:21,869
the queen it deserves.

912
01:57:26,624 --> 01:57:29,669
By fairest blood,
it is done!

913
01:57:46,727 --> 01:57:49,480
And only
by fairest blood
is it undone.

914
01:58:46,162 --> 01:58:48,539
You can't have my heart.

915
02:00:00,403 --> 02:00:04,323
In the name
of all that is good
and just in this land

916
02:00:04,490 --> 02:00:06,450
I crown you queen.

917
02:00:49,076 --> 02:00:50,619
Hail to the Queen!

918
02:00:51,412 --> 02:00:53,289
Hail to the Queen!

919
02:00:53,664 --> 02:00:55,332
Hail to the Queen!

920
02:00:55,666 --> 02:00:57,334
Hail to the Queen!

921
02:00:57,668 --> 02:00:59,670
Hail to the Queen!
